Package com.googlecode.batchfb

Interface Summary
Batcher Interface to the Facebook APIs which allows you to define multiple requests (graph and fql) in advance and execute them in an optimal set of actual http calls to Facebook.
Later<T> Similar to java.concurrent.Future; allows a return value to be defined sometime in the future.
PagedLater<T> Adds the ability to enqueue the previous and next pages of Facebook's paginated data structures.
 

Class Summary
BinaryParam A parameter which includes a binary attachment.
FacebookBatcher Primary implementation of the Batcher interface.
FacebookCookie This will decipher and validate the OAuth 2.0 cookie you get from Facebook.
GraphRequest<T> Represents one graph request queued by the user.
GraphRequestBase<T> Common behavior for the requests that get batched at the top level.
Param A single key/value parameter to a Facebook API request.
QueryRequest<T> Represents one queued FQL query.
Request<T> Adds common characteristics for all types of batcher requests.
